COVID-19 Global Data Analysis

Project Overview
This project performs Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) on a global COVID-19 dataset.
The objective is to analyze worldwide COVID-19 trends, identify patterns in cases and deaths, and generate meaningful insights through data visualization.

Tools Used
* Python
* Pandas
* NumPy
* Matplotlib
* Seaborn
* Google Colab

Dataset
Worldometer Coronavirus Daily Data Dataset

Project Tasks
* Data Cleaning
* Missing Value Handling
* Exploratory Data Analysis
* Data Visualization
* Insight Generation

Key Findings
* USA recorded the highest cumulative COVID-19 cases.
* USA also recorded the highest cumulative deaths.
* Global COVID-19 cases increased continuously throughout the pandemic.
* Strong positive relationships exist between cases and deaths.
* A small number of countries accounted for a large share of global cases.

